      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "These experiences highlight the power of the human mind's associative patterns, as it is highly capable of weaving together recent observations, like that billboard, into recurring dream narratives. While no scientific evidence suggests companies use billion-dollar technology to literally beam ads into people's brains, the brain actively seeks creative explanations for random environmental cues. It is completely normal for people to feel paranoid when vague subconscious fears become so specific and seemingly targeted, so speaking with a healthcare professional could provide peace of mind and help ground your reality.",
      "source": "target",
