      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's exactly what they want you to think, right? that it's just 'associative patterns' and 'coincidence'. if a company actually developed a way to slip sub-liminal cues into digital signals or something so it hits people while they sleep, they'd definitely deny it ever exists. it feels way too intentional to be a coincidence. how can you be so sure there isn't some kind of tech behind it that just isn't public yet?",
