      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely understandable why such a specific Feeling creates such a strong sense of paranoia, even though there is no scientific evidence for technology intercepting or influencing human dreams. While companies certainly use psychological tactics in advertising, there is no known mechanism by which subliminal signals from digital media can directly intrude upon the sleep cycle to alter dream content. Often, when the brain feels a threat of being manipulated, it amplifies minor coincidences into what feels like a targeted conspiracy. If this sense of being watched or controlled becomes overwhelming, focusing on grounding techniques or seeking professional support can help separate reality from these intense dream-based fears.",
      "source": "target",
